WHEREAS, {{#if employee}}Assignor is employed by Assignee and has developed certain inventions within the scope of employment{{/if}}{{#if purchase}}Assignor owns certain patents and patent applications that Assignee desires to acquire{{/if}}{{#if founder}}Assignor is a founder of Assignee and desires to assign intellectual property to the company{{/if}}{{#if corrective}}the parties wish to correct and confirm the assignment of certain patents{{/if}};

WHEREAS, Assignor desires to assign all right, title, and interest in and to such patents to Assignee;

NOW, THEREFORE, for good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged, the parties agree as follows:

1. ASSIGNMENT

1.1 Assignor hereby assigns, transfers, and conveys to Assignee all right, title, and interest in and to the following (collectively, the "Patents"):

{{patent_list}}

{{#if include_applications}}1.2 The Patents include all patent applications, provisionals, continuations, continuations-in-part, divisionals, reissues, reexaminations, and extensions related to the above.{{/if}}

{{#if include_future}}1.3 Assignor hereby assigns all future inventions and patent applications conceived, developed, or reduced to practice during the term of Assignor's employment with Assignee.{{/if}}

1.4 This assignment includes all rights of priority, all rights to sue for past infringement, and all proceeds from the Patents.

2. CONSIDERATION

{{#if employment}}2.1 The consideration for this assignment is Assignor's employment with Assignee and the compensation provided thereunder.{{/if}}

{{#if cash_payment}}2.1 In consideration for this assignment, Assignee shall pay Assignor the sum of ${{number cash_amount}} within thirty (30) days of the Effective Date.{{/if}}

{{#if equity}}2.1 The consideration for this assignment is the equity interest granted to Assignor in Assignee.{{/if}}

{{#if other}}2.1 The consideration for this assignment is [OTHER CONSIDERATION].{{/if}}

3. REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES

{{#if full_warranty}}3.1 Assignor represents and warrants that:
(a) Assignor is the sole owner of the Patents;
(b) Assignor has full right and authority to assign the Patents;
(c) The Patents are free of all liens and encumbrances;
(d) Assignor has not previously assigned the Patents;
(e) To Assignor's knowledge, the Patents are valid and enforceable.{{/if}}

{{#if limited_warranty}}3.1 Assignor represents and warrants that Assignor has not previously assigned the Patents to any third party.{{/if}}

{{#if no_warranty}}3.1 This assignment is made on a "quitclaim" basis without any representations or warranties whatsoever.{{/if}}
